{
  "texts": [
    "For our fitted models, we report explained deviances of: 85.8% (UA over RU), 90.5% (UA over EN) and 90% (RU over EN).",
    "The coefficients of a logistic regression, as employed here, must be interpreted with respect to changes in the odds (also known as odds ratio).",
    "The odds ratio is defined as odds = p/(1p).",
    "Hence, it describes how likely an event is going to happen compared to not happen.",
    "In this setting, it describes how likely it is to tweet in language 1 over language 2."
  ]
}